[1] Global update (Afghanistan, Angola, Ghana)
Date: Thu 22 Aug 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus weekly update as of 22 Aug 2019, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 1
Environment: 1

Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2019: 66
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 33

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 2
Environment: 0
Others: 2

Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2019: 53
Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2018: 104

Headlines
- Nigeria marked 3 years since the last case of wild poliovirus (WPV) was detected within its borders. Because Nigeria is the last polio-endemic country in Africa, this milestone opens the door for the potential WPV-free certification of the entire WHO AFRO region after the Africa Regional Certification Commission (ARCC) evaluation as early as mid-2020. While this is an important programmatic milestone, the region has not yet been certified polio-free, and it will be critical for [the] polio programme to maintain momentum.

Summary of new viruses this week:
- Afghanistan - 1 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case;
- Pakistan - 1 WPV1-positive environmental sample;
- Angola - 1 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) case;
- Ghana - 1 [cVDPV2] case.

Afghanistan
- 1 WPV1 case has been reported in the past week from Chora district, Uruzgan province, with onset of paralysis on [16 Jul 2019]. There are 13 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. [There] were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.
- No WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week.

Pakistan
- No WPV1 cases were reported in the past week. There are 53 WPV1 cases in 2019, and 12 WPV1 cases were reported in 2018.
- 1 WPV1-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week from Quetta district, Balochistan province. The samples were collected on [28 Jul 2019].

Nigeria
- No cases of cVDPV2 were reported in the past week. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week.

Lake Chad
- No case of cVDPV2 has been reported in the past week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018) and Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord).
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Ghana
- 1 cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week from Chereponi district, Northern province, with onset of paralysis on [23 Jul 2019]. This is the 1st cVDPV2 case in 2019. Earlier, a cVDPV2 was isolated from an environment sample collected on [11 Jun 2019] from the Northern province. Both the isolates are linked to [the] Jigawa cVDPV2 outbreak in Nigeria.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.

Benin
- No cases of cVDPV2 case were reported in the past week. There is 1 cVDPV2 case reported in 2019 so far.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
- No cases of cVDPV2 have been reported the past week. There were 20 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2018. DRC is currently affected by 9 separate cVDPV2 outbreaks: 1 each originated in Haut Katanga, Mongala, Sankuru, Tanganika, Tshopo, Kasai, Kasai Central, and 2 in Haut Lomami provinces.

Angola
- 1 case of cVDPV2 has been reported this week in Amboim district, Kwanza Sul State. The onset of paralysis was on 12 Jul 2019. There is a total of 6 cVDPV2 cases from 3 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic (CAR)
- There are 4 reported cases from 4 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019. Additional confirmed cVDPV2 community contacts have been reported in CAR.
- No environmental samples were reported.

Horn of Africa
- No case of cVDPV2 has been reported in the past week.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3, and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. cVDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in one environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There is also one reported case of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia, with onset on 20 May 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of cVDPV1 were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of cVDPV2 outbreak has been reported this week. There was one case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No cVDPV1 cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No case of cVDPV1 has been reported. There are 3 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 21 Aug 2019:
Total global cases in 2019: 66 (compared with 14 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in endemic countries in 2019: 66 (compared with 14 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in nonendemic countries in 2019: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018)

- Afghanistan: 13 cases in 2019 (compared with 11 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 16 Jul 2019
- Pakistan: 53 cases in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Jul 2019
- Nigeria: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Aug 2016

Total global WPV1 cases in 2019: 66
Total global WPV1 cases in 2018: 33

Officially reported cVDPV cases as of 21 Aug 2019:
- Angola : 6 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 12 Jul 2019
- Benin: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 7 Jul 2019
- Central African Republic: 4 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 23 Jun 2019
- China: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 25 Apr 2019
- Democratic Republic of the Congo: 17 cases in 2019 (compared with 11 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 5 Jul 2019
- Ethiopia: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 20 May 2019
- Ghana: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 23 Jul 2019
- Indonesia (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 27 Nov 2018
- Mozambique: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Oct 2018
- Myanmar (type 1): 3 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 14 Jun 2019
- Niger: 1 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 3 Apr 2019
- Nigeria: 15 cases in 2019 (compared with 6 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 20 Jun 2019
- Papua New Guinea (type 1): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 18 Oct 2018
- Somalia (type 2): 3 cases in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 8 May 2019
- Somalia (type 3): 0 case in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 7 Sep 2018

Total global cVDPV cases in 2019: 53
Total global cVDPV cases in 2018: 104

