[The good news is that it is now 3 years since the last case of WPV-associated paralysis was confirmed in Nigeria, and in turn on the African Continent. The not so good news is that the WPV continues to circulate in Afghanistan (and Pakistan, although there were no newly confirmed cases reported by Pakistan in the past week).

Other not so good news is that cVDPV continues to be a problem in Africa and elsewhere in the world. Angola has confirmed one new cVDPV2-associated paralysis, and Ghana has confirmed one case of cVDPV2-associated disease.

As done in previous posts, to visualize all of this activity, I am putting links to HealthMap/ProMED-mail maps of countries with poliovirus activity during the past 12 months below. The size of the list remains impressive now with 19 countries -- 12 in Africa, 5 in Asia, and 2 in the Western Pacific.

